==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: ethane
<hw>eth"ane</hw> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧th"⟦amac⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Ether</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A gaseous hydrocarbon,
<chform>C2H6</chform>, forming a constituent of ordinary illuminating
gas. It is the second member of the paraffin series, and its most
important derivatives are common alcohol (ethyl alcohol), acetaldehyde,
ether, and acetic acid. Called also
<altname>dimethyl</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>ethanol</ent>⟦br⟧
